                                                                  9915 1451
  Models and parameters used in the CCONE/7/ calculation          9915 1451
  1) Coupled channel optical model                                9915 1451
     Levels in the rotational band were included. Optical model   9915 1451
     potential and coupled levels are shown in Table 1.           9915 1451
                                                                  9915 1451
  2) Two-component exciton model/10/                              9915 1451
    * Global parametrization of Koning-Duijvestijn/11/            9915 1451
      was used.                                                   9915 1451
    * Gamma emission channel/12/ was added to simulate direct     9915 1451
      and semi-direct capture reaction.                           9915 1451
                                                                  9915 1451
  3) Hauser-Feshbach statistical model                            9915 1451
    * Moldauer width fluctuation correction/13/ was included.     9915 1451
    * Neutron, gamma and fission decay channel were included.     9915 1451
    * Transmission coefficients of neutrons were taken from       9915 1451
      coupled channel calculation in Table 1.                     9915 1451
    * The level scheme of the target is shown in Table 2.         9915 1451
    * Level density formula of constant temperature and Fermi-gas 9915 1451
      model were used with shell energy correction and collective 9915 1451
      enhancement factor. Parameters are shown in Table 3.        9915 1451
    * Fission channel:                                            9915 1451
      Double humped fission barriers were assumed.                9915 1451
      Fission barrier penetrabilities were calculated with        9915 1451
      Hill-Wheler formula/14/. Fission barrier parameters were    9915 1451
      shown in Table 4. Transition state model was used and       9915 1451
      continuum levels are assumed above the saddles. The level   9915 1451
      density parameters for inner and outer saddles are shown in 9915 1451
      Tables 5 and 6, respectively.                               9915 1451
    * Gamma-ray strength function of Kopecky et al/15/,/16/       9915 1451
      was used. The prameters are shown in Table 7.               9915 1451
